annotations: Floating around in a vacuum of space

When I wrote this song I was channeling that moment of disillusionment when this faith in things, in people, in the world, starts to fade. In the song I liken the feeling to floating around in a vacuum of space, but this is really just a visual for when the magic trick is revealed and suddenly you don’t know what to believe in anymore. When the flaws in people and in things you love are discovered, it’s a growing pain that’s both humbling and disappointing.

(From Consequence of Sound’s Track by Track, February 2018)

annotations: My girls could be a reference to her friends or her boobs, as some people like to you endearing terms to describe them. This accentuates her self confidence and charisma as even if they are her friends and she is complimenting them, people always respects people who respect others.
Baby, show me yours and then maybe I’ll show you mine
This could be a reference of sexting, or just sex in general, in terms of sexting it’s in reference to nudes, and how in modern day intimacy is simply transactional.
I got that box go like pop, pop, pop
Almost certainly bragging about her sexual prowess here, referring to her box (vagina) as popping.
I like to keep it loose, a freak in the sheets
I got a credit card and I use it all the time
Ironic – Caroline hopes to remain debt free unlike many peers who have no financial stability.
I got a bicycle, I’m cruising down the street
For Caroline, a bicycle is a suitable means of alternate transportation. To “cruise” down the street is to ride the bicycle with no concern to others – purely for self enjoyment.
I got the goochi, goochi, gooey, oozy, icky, oozy style
In an Instagram comment, Caroline says the lyrics are “goochi goochi” and do not reflect a “brand conscious” shoutout to a lifestyle she does not conform to.
